<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">
This genus resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Saxinis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Saxinis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Saxinis</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished by the epipleural lobe not well developed and from 
<taxonomicName authority="Monros, 1953" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Temnodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Temnodachrys</taxonomicName>
by the sides of the prothorax curved (strongly convergent towards the head); frons with deep medial pit; and distinct elytral pattern with transverse black bands on reddish base color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Austral region of Chile and Argentina.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">
<bibRefCitation author="Monros, F" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterists Bulletin" pageId="61" pageNumber="72" pagination="45 - 50" title="Some corrections in the nomenclature of Clytrinae." volume="7" year="1953 b">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Monrós">Monros</normalizedToken>
(1953b)
</bibRefCitation>
separated the genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Moldenke, 1970" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Saxinodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Saxinodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Saxinodachrys</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Monros, 1944" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cylindrodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindrodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cylindrodachrys</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Monros, 1953" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Temnodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Temnodachrys</taxonomicName>
, formerly considered within 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacordaire, 1847" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dachrys</taxonomicName>
. Currently monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
